Description: Implements Bayesian nowcasting models for incident disease cases
    using a censored-regression approach (Zepeda-Tello & Shaman, 2025). The
    reporting delay is modelled directly as a stochastic process, jointly with
    the epidemic dynamics, via the Guenther et al. (2021) censored likelihood.
    Inference uses RTMB (CppAD autodiff + Laplace approximation) with no Stan
    dependency. Supports multiple epidemic models (HSGP, AR1, SIR), multiple
    delay families (LogNormal, Gamma, GenGamma, Dirichlet), stratified data,
    two-stage multiple-imputation nowcasting, and full backtesting workflow.
